Download java
Install the jdk package
For env variables, run below commands in terminal
1. Find the java version installed on your machine and its location - run /usr/libexec/java_home - V
1. Go to location of variables -  vi ~/.zshrc
2. Hit I for inserting
3. export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home)
4. Hit Esc and then :wqÂ  and then ENTER
5. To save run - source ~/.bash_profile
6. To validate the path run - echo $JAVA_HOME
